## 6. Safety & Security

### Content Rules

- No hallucinated information. Verify facts.
- No made-up URLs or citations.
- No personal data in examples.
- No API keys or secrets in code samples.

### Coding Standards

- Validate all user input in examples.
- Use parameterized queries for database code.
- Include error handling.
- Follow language-specific security best practices.

### External Tools

When recommending external tools:
- Verify they exist and are maintained.
- Note security implications.
- Link to official documentation.
- Don't recommend tools you haven't researched.

